-- Stocks in South Africa Gain: Cashbuild, Litha Healthcare and Palabora Move
-- B y   R o n   D e r b y
-- 2010-09-21T16:13:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-21/stocks-in-south-africa-gain-cashbuild-firestone-litha-healthcare-move.html
South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All
Share Index  climbed for a second day, gaining 13.81, or 0.1
percent, to 28,724.74 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
South African market today.  Cashbuild Ltd.  (CSB SJ), a building-materials retailer,
advanced 2.2 rand, or 3 percent, to 75 rand. The company
reported a 19 percent increase in net asset value per share for
the year through June, while sales climbed 6 percent.  Litha Healthcare Group Ltd.  (LHG SJ), a South African
health-care company, jumped 8 cents, or 6.9 percent, to 1.24
rand, its biggest increase since May 12. The company said first-
half net income rose to 17.5 million rand ($2.5 million) from
14.2 million.  Palabora Mining Co.  (PAM SJ), the South African copper-
producing unit of Rio Tinto Plc, retreated 45 cents, 0.5
percent, to 96.49 rand. The company said the destruction of a
bridge in South Africa by a train derailment will prevent it
from exporting magnetite, a type of iron ore.  Pioneer Foods Ltd.  (PFG SJ), a South African food company,
fell 98 cents, or 2 percent, to 48.02 rand, a second day of
declines. The company said a financial settlement with the
country’s antitrust authorities over bread prices may surpass
provisions it made for the accord.  To contact the reporter on this story:
